 <body>
  <section name="Requirements">
   <span class='shortdesc'>What do you need to run Hippo CMS?</span>

  <div class='nav'>
   <table>
    <tr>
     <td>Web Browser</td>
     <td>
      <span class='web-48 icon-48'/>
     </td>
     <td> 
      Hippo CMS uses a client/server model. The client side runs in a web browser.
      <table>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <img src='../../images/firefox_logo_tiny.png' alt='Firefox logo'/>
        </td>
        <td>
         Firefox 1.5 just works, <a href='http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/'>3.0</a> is recommended and supported.
        </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <img src='../../images/internet_explorer_logo_tiny.png' alt='internet explorer logo'/>
        </td>
        <td>
          Internet explorer 6 just works, <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/netherlands/windows/products/winfamily/ie/default.mspx'>7</a> is recommended and supported.
        </td>
       </tr>
      </table>
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>Client OS</td>
     <td>
      <span class='OS-48 icon-48'/>
     </td>
     <td>The client side of Hippo CMS runs on every OS that runs one of the required web browsers.
         Windows XP and Vista and Linux Redhat, Suse and Ubuntu are supported.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>Client Hardware</td>
     <td>
      <span class='hardware-48 icon-48'/>
     </td>
     <td>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Intel Pentium 4
       </li>
       <li>
           512 MB Memory
       </li>
       <li>
          1024x768 screen resolution
       </li>
        <li>
         200 MB of available hard-disk space (not to be used by Hippo CMS, but to prevent the system from becoming too slow for Hippo CMS).
       </li>
      </ul>
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>Server OS</td>
     <td>
      <span class='OS-48 icon-48'/>
     </td>
     <td>
       Hippo CMS runs on all modern operating systems
       that run <a href='http://www.sun.com/'>Sun</a>'s 
       <span class='expires'>Java 6 (or 5)</span> 
       correctly, especially Microsoft Window systems after 2006 and
       <a href='http://www.linux.org/'>Linux</a> with a kernel >= 2.6.
     <div class='nav'>
      <table>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <img src='../../images/windows_logo_tiny.png' alt='MS windows logo'/>
        </td>
        <td>
         <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windows/windows-xp/default.aspx'>Microsoft Windows XP</a>
        </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
        <td>
         <img src='../../images/windows_logo_tiny.png' alt='MS windows logo'/>
        </td>
        <td>
         <a href='http://www.microsoft.com/windowsserver2003/default.mspx'>Microsoft Server 2003</a>
        </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
        <td>
          <a href='http://www.redhat.com/rhel/'><img src='../../images/redhat_logo_tiny.png' alt='Redhat logo'/></a>
        </td>
        <td>
          <a href='http://www.redhat.com/rhel/'>Redhat Enterprise Linux 5</a>
        </td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
        <td>
          <a href='http://www.novell.com/products/desktop/'><img src='../../images/suse_logo_tiny.png' alt='Suse logo'/></a>
        </td>
        <td>
          <a href='http://www.novell.com/products/desktop/'>SUSE Linux Enterprise Desktop 10</a>
        </td>
       </tr>
